
### MUMMER
```bash
	conda create -n mummer
	conda activate mummer
	conda install -c bioconda mummer
	conda deactivate
```
### CIRCOS. Run from: home/vegasa/miniconda3/envs/circos/bin
```bash
	conda create -n circos
	conda activate circos
	conda install -c bioconda circos
	connda deactivate
``` (edited) 

#When I need to run something in python, the conda environment has been created. I have used it to run the programs needed to generate the files used for circos. Once generated, get out of biopython and log in conda circos.

```
conda create -n biopython
conda activate biopython
conda install -c anaconda biopython
conda deactivate
```

